summary: 03/23/1993: A letter bomb exploded in the offices of Anglian Water in Scotland. The Scottish National Party (SNP) was suspected of conducting the attack, however there was no claim of responsibility. No injuries or casualties resulted from the incident.
motive: The assailants may have been protesting against a recent government move to privatize water.
addnotes: No claims of responsibility were made. The Scottish National Party (SNP) was suspected of being involved in the attack, as it has waged a campaign against the privatization of water. No injuries or casualties resulted from the attack.
scite2: Louise Jury, “Scottish Protesters Blamed For Letter Bomb At Water Authority,” The Guardian (London), March 24, 1993.
